details:
Case 162 is a 28 year-old male Singapore Citizen who had been in Indonesia from 29 February to 2 March. He is currently warded in an isolation room at NCID. He is linked to Case 142.

He reported onset of symptoms on 7 March. As he had been identified as a contact of Case 142, he was referred by MOH to National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID) on 9 March. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 9 March afternoon.

Prior to hospital admission, he had visited a shop at 26 Jalan Membina. He stays at Kim Tian Road.
